TITLE: Creating Top-Level Elements and Views in LikeC4
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to define top-level elements like 'customer' and 'cloud' and create a landscape view. The model block declares the elements while the views block configures how they are visualized.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/apps/docs/src/content/docs/dsl/extend.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: likec4
CODE:
```
model {
  customer = actor 'Customer'
  cloud = system 'Cloud System'
}
views {
  view index of cloud {
    title "Cloud System - Landscape"
    include *
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Defining Basic Elements in LikeC4
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define basic elements with kinds and names in LikeC4. Shows specification of element types and creation of actor and service elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/apps/docs/src/content/docs/dsl/model.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: likec4
CODE:
```
specification {
  element actor // define a kind
  element service
}

model {
  // element of kind 'actor' with the name 'customer'
  actor customer
  // element of kind 'service' named as 'cloud'
  service cloud

  // also possible with '=' and the name goes first
  cloud = service
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Styling Element Kinds in LikeC4 Specification
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to style all elements of a specific kind using the 'style' block in the specification section. This example shows styling for 'user' and 'frontend' elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/apps/docs/src/content/docs/dsl/styling.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: likec4
CODE:
```
specification {
  element user {
    style {
      // every element of 'user' kind
      shape person // have 'person' shape
      color amber  // and amber color
    }
  }

  element frontend {    
    style {
      // every 'frontend' displayed as browser
      shape: browser // ':' is optional, but if you prefer
    }
  }
}
```

