TITLE: Traversing and querying the LikeC4 model
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to query and traverse the model including validation errors checking, element selection, relationship filtering, and view layout retrieval.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/apps/docs/src/content/docs/tooling/model-api.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { LikeC4 } from "likec4"

const likec4 = await LikeC4.fromSource(`....`)

// Validation errors
console.log(likec4.getErrors())

// Traverse the model
const model = likec4.computedModel()
model
  .element('cloud.backend.api')
  .incoming() // relationships incoming to the element
  .filter(r => r.tags.includes('http')) // filter by tags
  .map(r => r.source) // get source elements

const diagram = await likec4.layoutedModel().view('index')
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding Relationships in LikeC4 Model
DESCRIPTION: Defines relationships between elements in the model, including interactions between the customer, UI, and backend components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/apps/docs/src/content/docs/tutorial.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: likec4
CODE:
```
specification {
  element actor
  element system
  element component
}

model {
  customer = actor 'Customer'
  saas = system 'Our SaaS' {
    component ui
    component backend

    // UI fetches data from the Backend
    ui -> backend
  }

  // Customer uses the UI
  customer -> ui 'opens in browser'
}
```

