TITLE: Logging Errors with @likec4/log in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates error logging patterns using the loggable helper function. Shows two approaches: wrapping the error with loggable() or passing it as part of an object in the second argument.
SOURCE: https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/main/packages/log/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { loggable } from '@likec4/log'

try {
  throw new Error('Something went wrong')
} catch (error) {
  logger.error(loggable(error))
  // OR pass as second argument
  logger.error('An error occurred', { error })
}
```

